headline.main: JAPANESE IN RAID NEAR AUSTRALIA; Ten Planes Bomb Kupang on Timor -- Foes Press Dutch at Four Strongholds JAPANESE IN RAID NEAR AUSTRALIA

lead_paragraph: BATAVIA, Netherlands Indies, Feb. 1 -- Japanese bombers struck today at Netherland Timor, southernmost of the Indies, only 310 miles from the Australian coast, while Netherland troops battled landing parties at four points, including the Amboina naval base.
